9
00:01:23.720 --> 00:01:25.760
Let me introduce myself. I'm tall. slim.

10
00:01:25.840 --> 00:01:29.640
and have a foreign surname
that suggests charisma and mystery.

11
00:01:29.720 --> 00:01:31.200
Yes. it is really me.

12
00:01:31.280 --> 00:01:32.560
Emily Ratajkowski.

13
00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:36.640
If you'd ordered her on Wish.
this is what you'd get.

14
00:01:38.200 --> 00:01:41.000
When I die. I want her photo
on my tombstone.

15
00:01:41.080 --> 00:01:42.800
I'll be dead anyway.

16
00:01:43.320 --> 00:01:45.280
Who is she gonna sue?
The kids I don't have?

17
00:01:45.360 --> 00:01:48.200
I'd love to have sons.

18
00:01:48.280 --> 00:01:50.960
I'd love my sons to be obnubilated by me.

19
00:01:51.040 --> 00:01:52.320
totally obsessed.

20
00:01:52.400 --> 00:01:55.320
Like those men who look
at their partner after sex and say.

21
00:01:56.960 --> 00:01:58.640
"You'll never be like my mother."

22
00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:02.080
But daughters? Never.

23
00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:05.520
I wouldn't want a thinner version of me
without mental health issues

24
00:02:05.600 --> 00:02:06.760
to tell my husband.

25
00:02:06.840 --> 00:02:10.360
"Daddy. can you buy me this?"

26
00:02:10.440 --> 00:02:12.200
Go to work. you freeloader!

27
00:02:12.800 --> 00:02:14.600
Even though you're five.

28
00:02:14.680 --> 00:02:17.600
Let's hear it for female solidarity!

29
00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:24.520
Anyhow. for those of you
who don't know me.

30
00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:26.960
people who lack good taste.

31
00:02:27.560 --> 00:02:31.360
I was born in Rome
on the 28th of July 1987.

32
00:02:31.440 --> 00:02:33.040
Have you heard of Rome?

33
00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:36.720
The city where we solve our issues
by setting them on fire.

34
00:02:37.840 --> 00:02:39.080
Buses.

35
00:02:39.160 --> 00:02:41.440
Old bridges. Rubbish.

36
00:02:41.520 --> 00:02:45.080
People wishing to use contactless payment.
"Can I use my card?"

37
00:02:45.160 --> 00:02:46.240
"If you want to…"

38
00:02:49.160 --> 00:02:51.280
TV. Cinema. The Internet.

39
00:02:51.360 --> 00:02:54.040
I've been everywhere. except for jail.

40
00:02:54.120 --> 00:02:55.400
But it won't be long.

41
00:02:56.280 --> 00:03:00.000
This year I finally signed up for VAT.
I'm living the dream.

42
00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:02.480
Financial police. Living the dream.

43
00:03:02.560 --> 00:03:05.600
I've worked my way up the ladder.

44
00:03:05.680 --> 00:03:08.880
I have tolerated sexual harassment.
and I have harassed too.

45
00:03:10.280 --> 00:03:13.520
And finally. I reached some of my goals.

46
00:03:13.600 --> 00:03:19.000
I was featured on the list of 100
most successful women by <i>Forbes Italia.</i>

47
00:03:29.720 --> 00:03:33.240
Now. you'd say. "Wow. Michela. not bad."

48
00:03:33.320 --> 00:03:35.120
"You should be proud."

49
00:03:35.640 --> 00:03:39.840
"Now you're famous.
I bet your life has changed."

50
00:03:39.920 --> 00:03:42.000
"You finally turned a corner."

51
00:03:42.080 --> 00:03:42.920
Nope.

52
00:03:43.440 --> 00:03:46.440
When you become famous.
your life doesn't change.

53
00:03:46.520 --> 00:03:49.520
You're still the same piece of shit.
but now everyone knows it.

54
00:03:50.560 --> 00:03:53.160
Your life changes
if you wake up and you're a cat.

55
00:03:53.240 --> 00:03:55.040
Thank fuck your life has changed.

56
00:03:55.120 --> 00:03:56.440
Now you shit in a tray.

57
00:03:57.040 --> 00:03:59.240
It's a different lifestyle.

58
00:03:59.320 --> 00:04:01.560
I'm still doing the same things
I always did.

59
00:04:01.640 --> 00:04:04.640
Every morning. I wake up.
and I check my profile

60
00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:07.320
to see if the size of my belly

61
00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:08.920
now resembles a Fiat Qubo.

62
00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:14.920
I'm still doing the same things.

63
00:04:15.440 --> 00:04:17.240
but I have many new problems.

64
00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:20.520
I don't know. If I'm waiting in a deli

65
00:04:20.600 --> 00:04:22.160
and there's an old lady

66
00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:24.840
who's taking 40 minutes

67
00:04:24.920 --> 00:04:27.880
to buy some gorgonzola cheese.
and I'm there…

68
00:04:28.840 --> 00:04:31.160
She goes. "I'd like some gorgonzola!"

69
00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:34.480
"Also. a little ham

70
00:04:34.560 --> 00:04:36.760
for my grandson!"

71
00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:39.240
"Also. a Pfizer booster!"

72
00:04:39.760 --> 00:04:42.760
"And some more gorgonzola!"

73
00:04:42.840 --> 00:04:44.560
"For fuck's sake. lady!"

74
00:04:45.160 --> 00:04:47.960
"Leave some gorgonzola
for the rest of us."

75
00:04:48.040 --> 00:04:49.160
"We want some too."

76
00:04:49.240 --> 00:04:53.000
"If you want to scream like Robert Plant.
go sing 'Whole Lotta Love' outside

77
00:04:53.080 --> 00:04:54.480
and fuck right off."

78
00:04:54.560 --> 00:04:58.200
But if I say something like that.
the day after. news websites will claim

79
00:04:58.280 --> 00:05:00.320
that I invented the Holocaust.

80
00:05:01.360 --> 00:05:04.160
"Elderly people. Watch out
for COVID and Michela Giraud."

81
00:05:07.360 --> 00:05:09.320
I hope nobody got offended here.

82
00:05:09.400 --> 00:05:11.000
Are there elderly people here?

83
00:05:13.240 --> 00:05:14.080
Are there

84
00:05:15.840 --> 00:05:17.720
any Robert Plant fans?

85
00:05:18.880 --> 00:05:20.920
Is Robert Plant here?

86
00:05:22.960 --> 00:05:25.360
Great. so I didn't offend anyone. Great.

87
00:05:25.440 --> 00:05:27.920
At least you're not
like Demi Lovato's fans.

88
00:05:35.240 --> 00:05:38.680
When you're always in the media.

89
00:05:38.760 --> 00:05:41.680
you have to watch what you say.

90
00:05:42.240 --> 00:05:44.080
I speak from personal experience.

91
00:05:47.680 --> 00:05:50.080
It was 2021 AD. in the month of May.

92
00:05:50.160 --> 00:05:51.640
I read this story.

93
00:05:51.720 --> 00:05:56.200
"Demi Lovato. 'I am non-binary.
I want to be addressed as 'they.'"

94
00:05:56.280 --> 00:05:59.800
I have no clue what "non-binary" means.

95
00:05:59.880 --> 00:06:01.120
I could google it.

96
00:06:01.200 --> 00:06:03.520
but my fierce comedic brain turns on

97
00:06:04.040 --> 00:06:06.960
and starts thinking
about that magician guy on TV.

98
00:06:08.880 --> 00:06:10.080
Maybe you know him.

99
00:06:10.160 --> 00:06:13.200
The Divine Otelma
has several humanities degrees.

100
00:06:13.280 --> 00:06:16.600
He refers to himself by saying "we."
and he's a magician.

101
00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:18.560
like anyone with a humanities degree.

102
00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:24.080
So I came up with the following joke.

103
00:06:24.600 --> 00:06:27.720
"Demi Lovato wants to be addressed
as 'they.' like the Divine Otelma.'"

104
00:06:27.800 --> 00:06:30.320
I tell myself. "This is genius."

105
00:06:30.840 --> 00:06:32.120
You're a genius.

106
00:06:32.640 --> 00:06:35.240
You so deserve the satire award
you received in 2020.

107
00:06:35.760 --> 00:06:38.880
Of course. I could have googled
"non-binary."

108
00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:40.480
but I have won awards. jeez!

109
00:06:43.040 --> 00:06:44.680
Are you crazy?

110
00:06:45.600 --> 00:06:47.200
Of course.

111
00:06:49.520 --> 00:06:50.880
I mean. I could…

112
00:06:52.200 --> 00:06:56.600
I could have checked an online dictionary.

113
00:06:57.200 --> 00:06:59.880
but I have an award on my wall

114
00:06:59.960 --> 00:07:03.040
between a crucifix
and a naked poster of Tom Hardy.

115
00:07:04.040 --> 00:07:05.080
Do you get me?

116
00:07:05.720 --> 00:07:08.760
In the end. I write this joke.

117
00:07:08.840 --> 00:07:10.960
"Demi Lovato says
she wants to be addressed

118
00:07:11.040 --> 00:07:12.720
as 'they.' like the Divine Otelma."

119
00:07:12.800 --> 00:07:16.200
I post it on Facebook.
and people are like.

120
00:07:16.280 --> 00:07:18.640
"You're awesome." "Genius."

121
00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:21.600
So. with such solid backing.

122
00:07:21.680 --> 00:07:23.040
I post the joke on Twitter.

123
00:07:28.200 --> 00:07:29.200
Yes. my friend.

124
00:07:30.040 --> 00:07:31.480
I posted it on Twitter.

125
00:07:33.640 --> 00:07:37.080
And after. I did something
incredibly smart.

126
00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:38.920
I turned my phone off.

127
00:07:40.680 --> 00:07:42.160
And I went out.

128
00:07:42.240 --> 00:07:44.520
I enjoyed real life.

129
00:07:44.600 --> 00:07:48.520
I thought. "The sun is out.
The kids are playing."

130
00:07:48.600 --> 00:07:51.080
"There's that old lady
with her gorgonzola."

131
00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:52.760
"The world is wonderful."

132
00:07:53.280 --> 00:07:54.480
I catch my train.

133
00:07:55.160 --> 00:07:56.480
I turn the phone back on…

134
00:07:57.200 --> 00:07:58.920
A barrage of insults.

135
00:07:59.720 --> 00:08:00.880
Like I was

136
00:08:02.240 --> 00:08:04.280
Britney Spears's dad.

137
00:08:05.080 --> 00:08:06.960
"You deserve to die!

138
00:08:07.040 --> 00:08:09.640
You fucking straight piece of shit"!

139
00:08:09.720 --> 00:08:12.360
By CutePie96.

140
00:08:12.880 --> 00:08:15.200
"Just die. you loser"!

141
00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:17.120
"I'll dance on your straight grave"!

142
00:08:17.200 --> 00:08:19.760
By CakeLover2001.

143
00:08:19.840 --> 00:08:22.560
Some of these people
wrote incredibly heavy stuff

144
00:08:22.640 --> 00:08:25.160
but had super cute profile photos.

145
00:08:27.320 --> 00:08:31.200
In the end. I thought.
"Okay. maybe I put my foot in it."

146
00:08:34.520 --> 00:08:38.760
"Let's just check
the meaning of 'non-binary.'"

147
00:08:41.080 --> 00:08:41.920
So I…

148
00:08:42.640 --> 00:08:43.560
After the fact.

149
00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:55.280
And I find out that the term "non-binary"
is something to do with the LGBTQI world

150
00:08:55.360 --> 00:08:59.760
and not. as I thought.
some Scientology-like thing

151
00:09:00.480 --> 00:09:02.880
or a fad diet. like the Dukan.

152
00:09:03.640 --> 00:09:07.160
I went from your fun-loving.
slightly mental Michela

153
00:09:07.240 --> 00:09:09.720
to the serial killer of M.

154
00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:15.520
I unwittingly made a joke
that offended the LGBTQI community

155
00:09:15.600 --> 00:09:19.480
on the eve of the release of a movie
about the LGBTQI community that I was in.

156
00:09:24.080 --> 00:09:27.400
Let's just say I got a call
from the press agency:

157
00:09:27.480 --> 00:09:29.080
"Hello? Is this Giorgia Meloni"?

158
00:09:31.120 --> 00:09:32.560
They wanted to remove me

159
00:09:32.640 --> 00:09:36.080
and digitally replace me
with a less compromised actor.

160
00:09:36.160 --> 00:09:37.280
Kevin Spacey.

161
00:09:46.360 --> 00:09:47.360
Who. me?

162
00:09:47.440 --> 00:09:50.240
I've always dreamed of being a cross

163
00:09:50.320 --> 00:09:53.440
between Madonna. Lady Gaga.
and RuPaul riding across a rainbow.

164
00:09:54.640 --> 00:09:57.640
After quite a long three hours. I think.

165
00:09:57.720 --> 00:09:59.680
"Michela. be your usual bright self."

166
00:10:00.800 --> 00:10:03.520
"You wrote so many amazing jokes
in your life…"

167
00:10:08.040 --> 00:10:10.960
"You wrote so many amazing jokes
in your life…"

168
00:10:14.640 --> 00:10:18.800
"You didn't know
that this one would hurt people."

169
00:10:18.880 --> 00:10:21.680
So I delete the joke. And I must say that…

170
00:10:21.760 --> 00:10:23.360
Another barrage of insults.

171
00:10:23.880 --> 00:10:26.760
Like I was Britney Spears' mom!

172
00:10:26.840 --> 00:10:29.800
Deleting the tweet didn't solve anything.

173
00:10:29.880 --> 00:10:31.760
and I pissed everyone off.

174
00:10:32.720 --> 00:10:35.120
This will end up being on my tombstone.

175
00:10:35.200 --> 00:10:37.520
"She pissed everyone off."

176
00:10:37.600 --> 00:10:39.480
Underneath Emily Ratajkowski's photo.

177
00:10:39.560 --> 00:10:41.080
I get messages like.

178
00:10:41.640 --> 00:10:45.400
"Shame on you. Michela.
You coward. You suck."

179
00:10:45.480 --> 00:10:48.800
"You bowed to the culture
of the politically correct."

180
00:10:48.880 --> 00:10:51.680
What would satire say?
And Aristophane? And Lenny Bruce?

181
00:10:51.760 --> 00:10:54.000
How do I know? Lenny Bruce is dead.

182
00:10:54.600 --> 00:10:56.200
"Hello. Michela? Hi."

183
00:10:56.280 --> 00:10:58.880
"Fancy doing a Live on Insta
with Alessandro Zan.

184
00:10:58.960 --> 00:10:59.840
the guy you hate.

185
00:10:59.920 --> 00:11:02.400
about his bill against
homo-and trans-phobia?"

186
00:11:02.480 --> 00:11:04.440
I'm not Pillon.

187
00:11:04.520 --> 00:11:07.160
Fine. I wrote a joke.

188
00:11:07.240 --> 00:11:10.800
I didn't only put up an Insta post
supporting the Zan bill.

189
00:11:10.880 --> 00:11:11.920
No!

190
00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:13.640
I did a lot more than that!

191
00:11:13.720 --> 00:11:17.080
I posted a video
with "Zan" written on both my hands.

192
00:11:17.160 --> 00:11:18.200
A double Zan!

193
00:11:18.280 --> 00:11:19.240
Oh!

194
00:11:19.320 --> 00:11:21.240
Could I be more supportive?

195
00:11:22.240 --> 00:11:25.760
But that's not all. Then they said.

196
00:11:25.840 --> 00:11:27.440
"Don't you worry. Michela."

197
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:30.920
"We'll always support freedom of speech."

198
00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:31.920
Signed.

199
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:33.520
L'Europa con Salvini party.

200
00:11:35.480 --> 00:11:41.480
It was like that time I read the comment.
"Michela. you rock."

201
00:11:41.560 --> 00:11:43.280
written by my ex's new girlfriend.

202
00:11:43.360 --> 00:11:45.880
He cheated on me with her
while I had COVID.

203
00:11:45.960 --> 00:11:48.320
People still stop me in the street to ask.

204
00:11:48.400 --> 00:11:50.880
"Michela. remember
when you went right-wing?"

205
00:11:51.800 --> 00:11:55.360
I am living proof of Andy Warhol's saying.

206
00:12:00.400 --> 00:12:03.080
But it was fun
to be a fascist for 15 minutes.

207
00:12:03.160 --> 00:12:05.120
Black does slim you down.

208
00:12:07.160 --> 00:12:08.000
However…

209
00:12:14.520 --> 00:12:17.160
I did find out something else too.

210
00:12:17.240 --> 00:12:21.480
I found out that being defended
was worse than being attacked.

211
00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:24.800
It's like getting a bukkake

212
00:12:25.320 --> 00:12:27.400
as you're having lunch with your parents.

213
00:12:28.080 --> 00:12:30.280
It's a cool thing. but at the wrong time.

214
00:12:32.720 --> 00:12:36.720
Being at the center of a Twitter shitstorm
is quite the constipating experience.

215
00:12:36.800 --> 00:12:40.160
It's like being on a FlixBus
with no brakes

216
00:12:40.240 --> 00:12:42.320
with a reggaeton-loving driver.

217
00:12:42.400 --> 00:12:46.560
And you're forced to sit there
and listen to. <i>"Loco loco…"</i>

218
00:13:00.840 --> 00:13:01.720
Enough!

219
00:13:01.800 --> 00:13:04.000
How <i>loco</i> can you be?

220
00:13:04.080 --> 00:13:08.280
If you're <i>loco.</i>
you're clearly out there already.

221
00:13:08.360 --> 00:13:10.480
But no. being<i> loco</i> just once isn't enough.

222
00:13:10.560 --> 00:13:12.520
You want to be<i> loco loco.</i>

223
00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:15.520
You want to go beyond <i>loco</i> reiteration.

224
00:13:15.600 --> 00:13:18.360
What could you do that is so <i>loco?</i>

225
00:13:18.440 --> 00:13:21.720
Will you help grandma with her digital ID?
Pay your taxes?

226
00:13:22.240 --> 00:13:25.080
Go to the residents association meeting
without a weapon?

227
00:13:25.160 --> 00:13:26.840
What?

228
00:13:26.920 --> 00:13:27.800
You go!

229
00:13:28.360 --> 00:13:29.200
However…

230
00:13:31.760 --> 00:13:32.600
However…

231
00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:39.160
I've got to say.

232
00:13:39.880 --> 00:13:42.720
fame does have its positives.

233
00:13:42.800 --> 00:13:45.840
You see.

234
00:13:45.920 --> 00:13:48.400
you get free stuff such as…

235
00:13:49.560 --> 00:13:52.320
T-shirts. moisturizers. slimming teas…

236
00:13:53.920 --> 00:13:55.840
Not that I need those.

237
00:13:57.080 --> 00:14:02.000
You get invited to be a guest on TV shows

238
00:14:02.080 --> 00:14:04.320
with very flattering emails.

239
00:14:04.840 --> 00:14:08.680
I remember I once got this email.
"Hi. Michela."

240
00:14:09.360 --> 00:14:12.440
"We are totally in love with your work."

241
00:14:12.520 --> 00:14:14.600
"We adore you. You're such a role model."

242
00:14:14.680 --> 00:14:18.040
"We'd like to have you discuss
something you care about."

243
00:14:18.120 --> 00:14:20.960
"We'd like you to come on the show
to talk about the fact

244
00:14:21.040 --> 00:14:24.680
that. even though you're not stick-thin.

245
00:14:24.760 --> 00:14:28.920
you keep living your life
and doing your thing."

246
00:14:32.520 --> 00:14:36.400
When I read this email. in my head.

247
00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:41.440
I heard it spoken out loud
with the sender's local accent.

248
00:14:41.520 --> 00:14:43.680
this show's writer…

249
00:14:43.760 --> 00:14:47.120
I love her accent
and the city she comes from…

250
00:14:47.200 --> 00:14:48.480
"Hi. Michela!"

251
00:14:48.560 --> 00:14:50.160
"You're the top!"

252
00:14:50.240 --> 00:14:52.920
"Would you like to come on our show

253
00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:56.120
and talk about how.
even though you're a ball of lard.

254
00:14:56.200 --> 00:15:01.000
you refuse to shoot yourself
in the head like Kurt Cobain?"

255
00:15:01.520 --> 00:15:04.120
