we'll never become poor like he is!"

867
00:50:45.720 --> 00:50:47.240
This one time.

868
00:50:47.320 --> 00:50:51.320
a friend of mine.
who's not exactly a Greek god.

869
00:50:51.400 --> 00:50:54.280
knocked on the door.
and my sister went to open it.

870
00:50:54.360 --> 00:50:55.800
And she did this.

871
00:51:11.280 --> 00:51:13.360
"Wow. you're really ugly."

872
00:51:14.840 --> 00:51:16.360
She slammed the door in his face.

873
00:51:16.440 --> 00:51:18.800
But ten minutes later. he was still there.

874
00:51:23.200 --> 00:51:26.720
My sister is very determined.

875
00:51:26.800 --> 00:51:30.240
If she wants something.
she really wants it.

876
00:51:30.320 --> 00:51:31.800
She's like Kim Jong-un.

877
00:51:32.480 --> 00:51:34.800
You could compare
the atmosphere in North Korea

878
00:51:34.880 --> 00:51:36.960
to the one at my house

879
00:51:37.040 --> 00:51:39.200
whenever we had lunch together.

880
00:51:39.800 --> 00:51:43.480
One year. for Easter.
we went to this holiday farm in Tuscany.

881
00:51:43.560 --> 00:51:48.960
I was so proud to have booked
a secluded little spot.

882
00:51:49.040 --> 00:51:50.480
basically in the fireplace.

883
00:51:51.640 --> 00:51:54.720
Eventually. we get to dessert.

884
00:51:54.800 --> 00:51:55.800
still unscathed.

885
00:51:56.400 --> 00:51:58.480
The place is so peaceful.

886
00:51:58.560 --> 00:51:59.680
And then. a child.

887
00:52:01.240 --> 00:52:03.160
a fucking child.

888
00:52:04.480 --> 00:52:05.520
stands up

889
00:52:07.160 --> 00:52:09.320
and starts singing like this.

890
00:52:17.680 --> 00:52:20.080
And the room goes. "Oh!"

891
00:52:20.600 --> 00:52:21.840
This is me.

892
00:52:21.920 --> 00:52:23.280
And my father.

893
00:52:23.360 --> 00:52:25.040
My mom. And my sister…

894
00:52:32.000 --> 00:52:33.080
"I want to sing."

895
00:52:34.480 --> 00:52:36.520
"No. No. darling. no."

896
00:52:36.600 --> 00:52:39.800
"There's no need to sing. really."

897
00:52:39.880 --> 00:52:41.840
"You have so many gifts."

898
00:52:41.920 --> 00:52:43.200
"She's just a child."

899
00:52:43.280 --> 00:52:48.520
"You don't need to show her up.
Let her sing."

900
00:52:48.600 --> 00:52:50.080
And my sister. "All right."

901
00:52:50.160 --> 00:52:51.160
And the child…

902
00:53:01.840 --> 00:53:02.680
And my sister…

903
00:53:44.520 --> 00:53:46.800
You'd think

904
00:53:46.880 --> 00:53:48.280
that the room would go…

905
00:53:50.480 --> 00:53:51.560
No!

906
00:53:51.640 --> 00:53:53.320
People are petrified.

907
00:53:54.520 --> 00:53:56.240
A lady behind me.

908
00:53:56.320 --> 00:53:57.240
Her husband.

909
00:53:57.320 --> 00:53:59.040
The roast on their plate.

910
00:54:01.200 --> 00:54:04.160
And then I became a teenager.

911
00:54:04.240 --> 00:54:08.560
As a teenager. I would wake up and say.

912
00:54:09.600 --> 00:54:10.840
"I'm alive."

913
00:54:10.920 --> 00:54:11.880
"Unfortunately."

914
00:54:13.120 --> 00:54:15.680
My number one enemy was the mirror.

915
00:54:16.520 --> 00:54:18.880
I'd look at trucks on the road

916
00:54:18.960 --> 00:54:21.200
with a heart filled with hope. not fear.

917
00:54:23.720 --> 00:54:24.760
And…

918
00:54:31.680 --> 00:54:33.560
You see. at that time.

919
00:54:33.640 --> 00:54:35.880
I used to spend my summers

920
00:54:35.960 --> 00:54:38.520
in a snobbish place just outside Rome

921
00:54:38.600 --> 00:54:42.080
populated by cool. snobby kids
with their little cliques.

922
00:54:42.160 --> 00:54:45.160
And I would hide in the bushes

923
00:54:45.240 --> 00:54:48.800
like some offshore bank account in Fiji.

924
00:54:49.520 --> 00:54:51.680
My sister. however. would say.

925
00:54:51.760 --> 00:54:53.000
"Guys!"

926
00:54:54.360 --> 00:54:56.840
"Wanna meet my sister? There she is!"

927
00:54:58.680 --> 00:55:00.240
"Michela!"

928
00:55:00.320 --> 00:55:02.640
"Wanna be friends with these guys?"

929
00:55:02.720 --> 00:55:05.320
"Guys. my sister is super funny!"

930
00:55:05.400 --> 00:55:06.640
"Michela!"

931
00:55:06.720 --> 00:55:09.800
"Did you pee yourself?"

932
00:55:12.000 --> 00:55:15.000
Inside. I was dying.
Rotting like the Tiber.

933
00:55:17.200 --> 00:55:18.560
I'd say. "Sure."

934
00:55:19.080 --> 00:55:21.320
"Hi. guys. it's me. The normal sister."

935
00:55:23.480 --> 00:55:27.800
At 15. I'd fake the self-confidence
of a 30-something-year-old woman

936
00:55:27.880 --> 00:55:31.240
even though I didn't know
I had to remove a tampon's applicator.

937
00:55:40.160 --> 00:55:44.480
It's not easy having a disabled sibling.

938
00:55:44.560 --> 00:55:47.720
It's like when your sibling
is a rock star.

939
00:55:47.800 --> 00:55:51.640
Everyone expects you
to be something special.

940
00:55:51.720 --> 00:55:52.880
"All right.

941
00:55:52.960 --> 00:55:55.480
this one is disabled."

