985
00:58:04.200 --> 00:58:06.720
<i>Bamboleiro! Bamboleiro!"</i>

986
00:58:18.000 --> 00:58:20.160
"Maybe it's your parents' fault."

987
00:58:20.240 --> 00:58:21.760
"Are you transgender?"

988
00:58:22.760 --> 00:58:24.200
"Nothing to do with that."

989
00:58:24.280 --> 00:58:25.560
"Are you curvy?"

990
00:58:27.800 --> 00:58:29.080
"Are you Jewish?"

991
00:58:30.040 --> 00:58:31.240
"Are you Romani?"

992
00:58:31.800 --> 00:58:32.920
"Nothing to do…"

993
00:58:33.000 --> 00:58:35.320
"But you said your dad was from Naples."

994
00:58:37.120 --> 00:58:39.440
"Listen. don't you dare…"

995
00:58:39.520 --> 00:58:40.960
"Okay. I get it.

996
00:58:41.040 --> 00:58:43.160
but have you seen a nutritionist?"

997
00:58:43.760 --> 00:58:45.920
"Have you seen an exorcist?"

998
00:58:46.000 --> 00:58:48.400
"Have you sent her
to <i>Italia's Got Talent?"</i>

999
00:58:50.320 --> 00:58:51.520
"You know what?"

1000
00:58:51.600 --> 00:58:54.040
"I feel for your parents."

1001
00:58:54.120 --> 00:58:57.880
"They had one disabled child.
and they dared to try again."

1002
00:58:57.960 --> 00:59:00.960
"And you came along.
You're not exactly stick-thin."

1003
00:59:02.160 --> 00:59:03.160
"No offense."

1004
00:59:03.240 --> 00:59:05.440
"I just have chubby arms."

1005
00:59:05.520 --> 00:59:08.960
"Don't be so touchy! What did I say?"

1006
00:59:09.600 --> 00:59:10.600
"Listen.

1007
00:59:10.680 --> 00:59:14.440
I'm gonna confess something."

1008
00:59:14.520 --> 00:59:16.800
"It's such a difficult situation."

1009
00:59:17.440 --> 00:59:18.440
"My father…

1010
00:59:31.800 --> 00:59:33.440
has high cholesterol."

1011
00:59:46.520 --> 00:59:49.600
"Luckily. they gave him
the disabled parking permit."

1012
00:59:49.680 --> 00:59:52.120
"And he had to insist! Unbelievable!"

1013
00:59:52.200 --> 00:59:53.880
"I'll tell you the truth."

1014
00:59:53.960 --> 00:59:56.480
"Yes. my sister wears a colander
on her head."

1015
00:59:56.560 --> 01:00:00.400
When I was a kid.
I never saw her as different.

1016
01:00:00.480 --> 01:00:03.600
but I could see it in other people's eyes.

1017
01:00:04.120 --> 01:00:05.880
I could see their looks.

1018
01:00:05.960 --> 01:00:09.560
When we went somewhere. they'd move away.

1019
01:00:09.640 --> 01:00:12.560
And at one point. I started wondering.

1020
01:00:12.640 --> 01:00:16.600
