why are people avoiding us?"

1021
01:00:16.680 --> 01:00:18.880
"Why don't we get invited to parties?"

1022
01:00:18.960 --> 01:00:20.600
"Or to dinners?"

1023
01:00:20.680 --> 01:00:22.640
"Why do they look at us as if we were…

1024
01:00:24.480 --> 01:00:25.440
monsters?"

1025
01:00:33.600 --> 01:00:35.600
And my mom said.

1026
01:00:36.680 --> 01:00:38.400
"Don't worry. my darling."

1027
01:00:38.480 --> 01:00:40.280
"You see.

1028
01:00:41.680 --> 01:00:43.760
our head is like a saucepan."

1029
01:00:44.280 --> 01:00:47.320
"We throw in so much information."

1030
01:00:47.400 --> 01:00:49.880
"But your sister doesn't have a saucepan."

1031
01:00:50.680 --> 01:00:53.040
"She has a colander."

1032
01:00:56.920 --> 01:00:57.760
And…

1033
01:01:01.560 --> 01:01:04.680
since I used to play
with a colander on my head.

1034
01:01:04.760 --> 01:01:07.760
I asked. "Mom. do I have
the same syndrome she has?"

1035
01:01:07.840 --> 01:01:09.560
"No. you're just curvy."

1036
01:01:16.960 --> 01:01:17.960
Okay.

1037
01:01:18.720 --> 01:01:22.960
I'd like to dedicate this show

1038
01:01:23.520 --> 01:01:26.960
